The menu of a fat-addicted child: It doesn't eat breakfast and eats sausage for dinner
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have problems with overweight, with 9 percent of all students and 5 percent of all children being overweight.
Recent surveys proven - obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles.
This shows once again how important the milieu is for the healthy development of a person in which he grows up and are the examples that surround him.
On the tables of obese children, sausages are up to half more common on the table than in families where normal-weight children live.
More than 19 percent of overweight children had fries for dinner on the day before the enlightenment campaign under the motto "Obesity is no coincidence."
In families with fats, sport is not exactly one of the favorite activities, which also affects the majority of today's students - only 15 percent replied that their parents find themselves at least once a week time for active exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, with almost 900 children from primary schools surveyed across the Czech Republic.
This was already the second year of the campaign "Obesity is no coincidence", which is supported by the general health insurance and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12 thousand students from 4 and 8 have taken on the project. classes part.
Unhealthy diet and lack of exercise in the family are decisive factors that are responsible for the frighteningly increasing number of children with excess weight or even obesity.
"Only half of the children surveyed, for example, cited eating five times a day, in the mode of breakfast-second-lunch-Vesper-evening bread - one of the main prerequisites for a healthy diet," according to one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that relative small things, such as the family’s regular breakfast time, are also important for a child’s healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 percent of the families of the students have breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone eats breakfast for themselves.
Worst of all was the finding that in every tenth family is not eaten at all.
Breakfast is considered the cornerstone of a healthy daily diet.
The survey test revealed, among other things, that you consume in the families of overweight children much more often unhealthy fries.
And almost everyone - without regard to weight - drinks sweet sodas every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed play sports, only less than half of their parents do so - namely only 15 percent.
Create your own menu
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to put together their own meal plan out of offered opportunities for appetite and opinion.
“What Czech children between 12 and 15 prefer in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among her favorite dishes were many pastries, meat dishes and, of course, desserts.
"Alarming is above all the great popularity of sweet sodas," is emphasized in the final report to this survey.
At lunch, i.e. the main dish, pasta won just before poultry.
The children hardly liked legumes at all and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Moving towards health
At the same time, however, the survey also showed that the children are quite willing to change their eating habits if they get the right information.
"In the control group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the enlightenment of the enlightening lecture "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a significant shift in preferences towards principles of healthy eating," the results of the project said.
This was evident, for example, in the sweet limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
The children also ticked poultry or fish much more often in the questionnaire than the main course of the day and were ready to eat less dumplings or sweet food.
Professionals claim - a stylist must also be a good psychologist
In the introductory article on how stylists learn, I had a bit complained that that was a bit too much fabric for starters.
I didn’t know what was to come.
Lectures by three professionals from the industry, the clothing of problematic figures and a seminar on how this is going "on the pitch".
It's supposed to get worse.
The closer the exam approaches, the more information and practical tasks are ahead of us.
But even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is still fully occupied.
This time we debated with Director Alena (not a single man participates in the course) how to attract a woman who does not have an ideally proportioned figure.
And that's most of us, after all.
Some have a too short neck, others a too boyish figure without neat curves and still others are chubby.
It is up to the stylist to visually conceal broad shoulders, extend the neck or conjure up the necessary curves.
We also got tips on how to put on a woman type like Jennifer Lopez - so with big bosom, wide hip and narrow waist - pretty and figure-hugging, without her looking too provocative.
For example, if the difference between waist and hips is so great that the skirt or pants really do not fit, you should at least have a piece tailored to measure.
You will certainly not regret this, because well-fitting clothes are simply priceless.
In such a tailor-made skirt, you feel much better than in one off the pole, which always slips up and down, stands out at the waist, etc.
Boyish figures can in turn allow themselves to wear clothing with wrinkles, bulging, appliqués, embroidery or gathering.
With this amount of information and figure types, I’m glad I have a whole week to let everything go through my mind thoroughly.
And yet I am afraid that in view of the applied homework task, it is almost impossible to do.
Each of the course participants was assigned a celebrity, for which she should come up with suitable outfits - daywear and evening wear.
We should take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the corresponding star and his figure type.
I'm supposed to "put on" Miranda Kerr who you may know from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
Inside I cheer, because that is much better for me personally than, for example, to attract Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has probably gained about a hundred kilos in recent times (well, that's a bit exaggerated), or even the young Selena Gomez.
We should cut out the garments from magazines or search, print them out on the Internet and then edit them graphically.
In the "Moodboard", as the whole result is called, our very personal style and our relationship to the graphic design should be expressed.
It is very important to also think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only attracts the models purely physically, but also designs the so-called product page in the journals (according to the specific specification, for example trend handbags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about this.
But that's not until Sunday.
This means that a stylist must have a good overall view.
The Saturday lecture, which was filled with information about figure types, was equally spiced by three visitors from the industry:
by stylist Jan Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and that a stylist should be able to take advantage of this.
And sent-in stylist can work with a single piece of clothing in very different ways.
The magic word is variability.
For example, you can wear a trench coat as usual over the jeans, i.e. like a T-shirt or coat, but you can also wear it on your naked body, put on heel shoes and wear it as a dress.
It is enough to roll up the sleeves or the collar and the whole look looks very different.
"Play with it," he insisted.
But most of all, the following advice was appropriate to me: "First you have to know the rules perfectly."
"Only then are you allowed to hurt her," Jakub said.
Finally, I realize why we have to timpanize all these teachings, what you can combine with what and why, even if you often get to see completely different things in fashion journals.
Not to mention fashion shows.
Thanks to the photographer Ben, I now know that a stylist must have prepared much more clothing variants than he ultimately photographs.
So you have to be prepared for a fashion story with ten pages (i.e. ten outfits) to style at least fifteen.
And also that the clothing in the photo in combination with other accessories sometimes looks very different than in reality.
So you have to expect all this in the design of the outfit.
Jan Pokorný also confirmed that image and style sometimes make up half of the success.
You only need to look at Madonna, a not exactly brilliant singer, from whom image and marketing have made a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the services of a stylist are more reserved.
Even well-known personalities often consider this to be thrown out money (the main thing is that I bring something, what I look like is secondary).
And if one of us can be styled, then we should expect that he or she will almost certainly impose a completely different (smaller) size than he or she actually needs.
Then you only need to google to find with certainty that the tabloid press writes that the corresponding celebrity has closed or decreased again, etc.
Jan and Mario urged us on Sunday not to believe that a stylist only needs to focus on fashion and then "assemble" the outfit.
In his work, he must above all communicate with the people he styles and he must be a clever psychologist.
Assess people without getting involved and standing by his opinion.
“If any manager orders us to look at her wardrobe and add pretty pieces, then we can’t clear out the whole closet and tell her – my God, that’s terrible.”
"You have to find at least some commendable things to recommend what you can wear," says Mario.
He also showed us very specifically what such a so-called "space bag" must include.
So such a bag, which you button up at the waist and in which you carry all the necessary proprieties with you.
In addition to such clear things as scissors, unwinders for hair removal or safety pins, it also contains such utensils as a nylon thread (thus the stylist helps to photograph products, such as handbags or hats), special clips with which the clothes are gathered at the back, if it is too large (pins or other clamps are prohibited, so that the fabric does not break) and of course sewing tools.
However, so that we not only have to listen, but also try something in practice, we learned how to glue shoes properly.
Even when photographing in the studio, where the floor is level, you can damage the shoe sole, let alone the outside.
We glued and glued ourselves...
With the scissors you must not even touch the shoes, so that you do not damage them.
So you have to be really skillful.
Mario delighted me by praising my "creation" without restrictions.
The skill mentioned is not exactly my strength.
All of this was just the fraction of what we heard at the second weekend sequel course.
One thing has become clear to me by now - to devote yourself to styling at a professional level is not a breeze.
V Need for Speed: "The Run" - the illegal race across America
Review
The originally carefree ride becomes a routine ride to the early shift through a series of completely avoidable, dilettante error.
Although it was possible to fulfill the ambitions in large part, what good is it, if obviously no one wanted to do a little more.
Even before he came to the counters, the new part, with the subtitle "The Run," raised high expectations.
He promised to move the already-year-old game series "Need for Speed" a piece into a new dimension and in the playable demonstration examples he actually seemed to be not just one of many action racing games.
We were also curious about how the fitted passages in which the main protagonist gets out of the car and continues on foot.
But as you are used to with NFS, in the end, much is different than you expected.
Sure - potentially they're quite decent arcade races, but overall the game is diminished by some superfluous mistakes that have been more or less present in this series for a few years.
So they are actually no longer mistakes, but rather signs of an incomprehensible laziness of the game developers.
The adventure starts very well.
First, one is introduced to history, whose main character Jack has certain personal problems; the only solution seems to be to participate in an illegal race across America.
In San Francisco, i.e. on the West Coast, you sit down at the steering wheel - with the task of being the first to be in New York.
The basic idea includes a whole series of interesting elements.
The entire route is divided into ten stages and into more than fifty individual races.
This means that each race is held on a different track and that the individual stages take place in different, sufficiently different and interesting environment.
You don't have a moment the impression that game would offer the same thing over and over again.
Some environments are still extremely pretty to look at, although the technical level of the graphic does not go beyond that of the earlier parts of the series.
So nothing earth-shatting.
But the drive through the desert, through autumnal scenery or high up through deep snow-covered landscape looks very pleasant visually.
Every now and then, uncharacteristic elements bring a little variety to the individual races.
In the desert, for example, you are surprised by a desert storm that severely restricts the view.
In the mountains, on the other hand, you have to be hellishly careful not to be spilled by an avalanche.
By the way, the individual races are installed quite well in succession.
Only a few, but they are enough.
For a while you try to overtake the prescribed number of opponents (in principle a classic race), then you have time to catch up (classic race against the stopwatch), then a personal duel with a single opponent awaits you.
And the police also interfere, who want to screw up the whole thing.
A novelty is passages in which Jack leaves the car.
This is more about certain interactive animations in which Jack escapes from anyone and where the player has to help him by pressing the right button at the right moment.
So nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are much fewer such passages in the game than one would expect (specifically probably only three).
Ultimately, this is more of the advantage of the matter, because at least this element has no chance of getting boring - it belongs in the context of the above to the elements that make the game more varied.
The driving model progresses in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, from today’s point of view, it does not tear out trees, on the other hand, one could not claim that it would be bad.
If you are looking for realistic simulations, you have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model continues to do justice to an action-packed racing, although you could find better in the competition.
Until then, everything is in good order.
Real problems only arise after a certain time.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not quite O.K.
From a game of this kind, it is hardly to be expected to calculate complicated deformations and collisions, but if you have virtually no idea how the car behaves before any impact on any object, then obviously not everything is okay.
Typical example: When driving close overtaking or passing oncoming cars, you only "roam" the other car slightly in some places, but in other, almost identical situation you get into a slingshot and turn wild pirouettes.
Or drive the cart straight to scrap.
Thanks to the restart system, this does not matter anymore, but it is always annoying.
The restarts are solved like this: if you have total damage or land far off the track, then the game throws you back to the last indication of the track.
Only - in each race you only have five restarts.
When you have exhausted them, everything starts all over again..
So the restarts are more like a tool, in case something does not succeed, but you should not rely on it.
Sometimes, however, the restart does not even help, so nothing helps but to learn the critical section from the head.
What is extremely unpleasant is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some curves, for example, have to be driven through in a very specific way, otherwise you simply do not fit through.
Elsewhere, you always encounter "civilian" cars in the same configuration, whether you come first or fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is particularly annoying in situations when you see that the opponent passes two oncoming cars in front of a playful way, but until you get there yourself, the cars are already in such a position that you have to drive them around or brake them.
And it doesn’t matter when you get there, because everything is designed so that this situation is always close to your nose.
The opponents have other advantages.
In the whole game there are a few places where you are always overtaken by the same opponent at the same place and again without regard to the time.
The most crazy thing is at the end of the game on the long bridge that you pass in the opposite direction.
The opponent obviously has to overtake a here on devil come out.
And if he is already in front of you, then of course he takes the view, so that you drive your own car a few times in Klump.
Sure - you just want to make the game more exciting and exciting, but this intention is so clear that it quickly spoils the joy of the game.
And that’s a shame, because despite a simpler driving model, the game is quite entertaining and sometimes so action-packed that you almost no longer know where your head stands.
And in principle, it doesn't matter what "to blame" is - the concept with fifty unique routes, the arrangement of the races in a way that no boredom can arise, or something completely different...
An unusual idea is also the car change in the course of the races.
You must not overlook the gas stations on the track, because this is where you can change the car, although in most cases the car you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
The sports cars are well suited for the urban areas, the strong American sedans for the straight highways and exotic super sports cars for the technical rides, for example on the serpentines in the mountains.
Hand in hand with the mode of the game history also goes the task mode (challenges) - i.e. the races in the individual localities that you know from history.
Here there are not only medals, but also to gain experience points for your own profile, which is common to the tasks (challenges) and the story.
To get to the higher driver level, various items must be unlocked: from the car, to the backgrounds for the profile.
This is also associated with the online function Autolog, which compares, among other things, the own achieved results with those of other players and also ensures further collective functions.
One of other incomprehensible carvers is a situation in the last race of history.
Here you can get by car to a subway tunnel (meanwhile), where you rest in the dark on the rails long (mean).
On the speedometer, digits between 150 a 200 km/h (meaning), but there comes suddenly from behind a subway and drives one uncompromisingly to scrap.
In our editorial office, we will probably argue for a long time about whether this was a blackout of the game designers or whether the authors think we are so stupid.
The technical side is nothing overwhelming, but at least the overall visual impression is quite appealing in most cases and even brilliant here and there.
It is all the more annoying that at some exciting moments the refresh rate slows down and this is sometimes quite dramatic.
However, this applies in particular to accidents with a larger number of participants, where a continuous FPS is of no use anyway.
The sound reproduction is so far O.K. and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to appeal to a scale as wide as possible to young audiences, a soundtrack a lá "of everyone" was created - but who buys such a game because of the music?!
Need for Speed: The Run The feelings are rather mixed.
If the game were not diminished by the totally unnecessary mistakes mentioned above, we could have claimed with the breast tone of conviction that The Run is the best piece of NFS in recent years.
But that's how the game seems kind of unfinished.
In a great pleasure in itself, but you should be prepared for these mistakes with the power of airport headlights in the eye.
Concert of the "Students of the Velvet Revolution" with singing ensembles of the Charles University
The Festa Academica Festival now offers for the third time the combination of World Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution and this including the music experience.
In the course of the festival, the twenty specialist and university choirs will present themselves.
The focus of the festival is on the two concerts, which were on the 17th. November is taking place.
"The Karlsuniversität has a large share in the festival."
"Among the participants is also the choir of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanistic Studies and the Festival Committee also includes the Rector Václav Hampl," said Jakub Čaloun, Head of the Organizing Team.
The absolute highlight of the festival is the public concert of specialist school choirs, which will take place on the 17th. November from 2 p.m. on the square in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the composition of the important Czech jazz player Karel Růžička "Celebration Jazz Mass".
In the evening hours, the concert "Students of the Velvet Revolution" (Studenty sametu) takes place in the gala rooms of the Volkshaus in Vinohrady, where university choirs also perform, choirs of the Karlsuniversität not excluded.
Festa Academica is the goal not only to celebrate World Student Day and the 22. To commemorate the Velvet Revolution on the anniversary, but to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to promote the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Association of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Johannes-Kepler-Gymnasium.
The patronage of the entire event was given by Bohuslav Svoboda, the mayor of the capital Prague and Václav Hampl, the rector of Charles University.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20. November in Prague and in Pardubice.
In addition to festive concerts, the schedule also includes numerous music meetings, student happanings, matinees and other events.
Interested parties can find detailed information on the websites of the festival www.festaacademica.cz
