“For us from IBM, this long-term thinking means a continual movement towards the future.
IBM survived and was also successful for a whole century because it has remained true to its principles and did not shy away from changing everything else all around.
This allowed us to transform technologies, business and society over the course of our first century.
We hope to create even more in the next hundred years," Samuel J said. Palmisano, the current director of the company on the occasion of the anniversary.
Sophisticated system
Watson already operated social care of its employees in the 1930s - in a similar way to the entrepreneur Baťa in Czechoslovakia: The IBM people were one of the first American employees to have paid leave, insurance by the entrepreneur plus elegant uniforms as workwear and a well-thought-out remuneration system for the best newcomers and dealers.
