"From the beginning, IBM had the concept of an institution rather than a mere technology company," said Economist, the Harvard Business School professor and the author of a book about IBM, Rosabeth Moss Kanter.
"IBM is not a technology company, but a company that helps solve business problems using technology," added George Colony of consulting firm Forrester Research.
As the company itself points out, it is a difference to be present in the market or to shape it directly through this presence.
IBM - called "Big Blue" in the states of its logo because of family, has grown into one of the largest companies in the world in a century.
It's one of the most versatile technology companies ever - IBM develops hardware and software, infrastructures, hosting and consultation services in an incredible product breadth - from servers to nanotechnology.
Of all American technology companies, IBM owns the most patents and five of its employees have already been awarded the Nobel Prize.
His most famous inventions include, for example, ATMs, credit cards, financial swaps, barcode or even the floppy.
With approx. IBM was the second largest technology company (equal to Apple) this year, with it overtaking Microsoft for the first time since 1996.
Looking ahead
