He has a vision of how things could and should be.
Shortly after he had done all this, he went off and did it.
A quick look at seven remarkable sequences of the Lost Interview:
How he learned to run a company:
“Throughout the years in business, I always ask, ‘Why are you doing things?’ And the answer you always get is, "Oh, it's just made that way."
No one knows why he does what he does. No one in the business really thinks about things in depth.
